# DharmaDaily — Execution Plan

> **DharmaDaily** is a Hinduism-focused, AI-powered spiritual companion on WhatsApp that delivers personalised daily Rashi readings, curated Sanskrit scripture, and devotional challenges — all through a single morning message.

---

## Scope & Key Decisions

This plan adapts the broader "DailyDivine" concept with the following constraints:

| Decision | Choice |
|---|---|
| Faith scope | **Hinduism only** (Vedas, Upanishads, Bhagavad Gita, Ramayana, Puranas, Stotras) |
| App name | **DharmaDaily** |
| Languages (MVP) | **Hindi & English** |
| WhatsApp provider (MVP) | **Twilio WhatsApp API** (fastest setup; migrate to Meta Cloud API at scale) |
| AI model | **Anthropic Claude API (claude-sonnet-4-6)** |
| Backend | **Node.js + Express** |
| Database | **PostgreSQL via Supabase** |
| Scheduler | **BullMQ (Redis-backed)** — more reliable than node-cron for per-user timezones |
| Web dashboard | **Next.js (React)** |
| Hosting | **Railway** (backend + DB + Redis in one platform) |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **User to confirm:**
> 1. Are you planning to use your own Twilio / Meta WhatsApp account, or do you need guidance on setting one up?
> 2. Do you have an Anthropic API key, or should we stub AI calls during early development?
> 3. Preference on Supabase (hosted) vs. self-hosted PostgreSQL on Railway?
> 4. Should the web dashboard be deployed separately (e.g. Vercel) or alongside the backend on Railway?

---

## System Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph User
        WA[WhatsApp User]
        WEB[Web Browser]
    end

    subgraph External
        TWILIO["Twilio WhatsApp API"]
        CLAUDE["Claude API"]
    end

    subgraph Backend ["Railway"]
        API["Express API Server"]
        BULL["BullMQ Scheduler"]
        REDIS["Redis"]
        DB["PostgreSQL (Supabase)"]
    end

    subgraph Frontend ["Vercel / Railway"]
        NEXT["Next.js Dashboard"]
    end

    WA -- sends msg --> TWILIO
    TWILIO -- webhook --> API
    API -- sends reply --> TWILIO
    TWILIO -- delivers --> WA

    API -- prompt --> CLAUDE
    CLAUDE -- response --> API

    API <--> DB
    BULL <--> REDIS
    BULL -- triggers daily job --> API

    WEB --> NEXT
    NEXT <--> API
```

