## Phase 2 — WhatsApp Integration & Onboarding (Days 7–12)

### Goals
Connect Twilio WhatsApp webhook, build the conversational onboarding flow, and store user profiles.

### Onboarding Conversation Flow

```
User: "Hi" / "Namaste" / "Start"
Bot:  🙏 Namaste! Welcome to DharmaDaily — your personal spiritual companion.
      What should I call you?

User: "Parvi"
Bot:  Lovely to meet you, Parvi! 🙏
      What is your Rashi (zodiac sign)?
      1️⃣ Mesh (Aries)
      2️⃣ Vrishabh (Taurus)
      ... (all 12)
      
      Reply with the number.

User: "3"
Bot:  Mithun Rashi — noted! ♊
      Which language do you prefer?
      1️⃣ English
      2️⃣ हिन्दी

User: "1"
Bot:  Last question — when should I send your daily message?
      1️⃣ 6:00 AM
      2️⃣ 7:00 AM
      3️⃣ 8:00 AM
      4️⃣ Custom time (reply HH:MM)

User: "2"
Bot:  ✅ You're all set, Parvi!
      Starting tomorrow at 7:00 AM, you'll receive:
      ☀️ Your personalised Rashi reading
      📖 A sacred verse from Hindu scripture
      🔥 A daily spiritual challenge
      
      Type anything anytime to chat with me about dharma, 
      prayers, or life guidance. 🙏
```

### WhatsApp Template Message (for daily proactive sends)
```
🙏 Namaste {{1}}! — Day {{2}} 🔥

☀️ *{{3}} Rashi — Today's Reading*
{{4}}

📖 *Today's Verse*
_{{5}}_
— {{6}}

🔥 *Daily Challenge*
{{7}}

Reply to share your thoughts or ask me anything! 🙏
```
> Variables: `{{1}}` name, `{{2}}` streak, `{{3}}` rashi, `{{4}}` horoscope, `{{5}}` verse, `{{6}}` source, `{{7}}` challenge

#### Tasks
- [ ] Configure Twilio WhatsApp sandbox (or production number)
- [ ] Build `POST /webhook/whatsapp` — receives incoming messages
- [ ] Build `controllers/onboardingController.js` — state-machine for the onboarding flow
- [ ] Build `services/userService.js` — create/update user profiles in DB
- [ ] Submit WhatsApp message template for approval (Twilio console)
- [ ] Test: complete onboarding via WhatsApp, verify user saved in DB

