## Phase 4 — Scheduler & Streak System (Days 21–26)

### Goals
Implement the BullMQ-based scheduler for per-user daily sends and build streak tracking.

### Scheduler Design
- **Daily scan job** runs every hour (or every 30 min at scale)
- Queries users whose `deliveryTime` matches the current hour (in their timezone)
- Enqueues a `sendDailyMessage` job per user into BullMQ
- Job processor generates content (Phase 3 service), sends via Twilio, logs to `DailyMessage`
- Failed jobs retry up to 3 times with exponential backoff

### Streak Logic
| Event | Action |
|---|---|
| Daily message sent & user replies | `streakCount += 1`, update `lastInteraction` |
| User interacts with bot (any message) | Update `lastInteraction` |
| 2 consecutive days with no interaction | Reset `streakCount = 0` |
| Streak milestone (7, 21, 40, 108 days) | Send congratulatory message with badge emoji |

#### Tasks
- [ ] Set up Redis on Railway
- [ ] Build `jobs/dailyScanJob.js` — periodic scan for users to message
- [ ] Build `jobs/sendDailyMessageJob.js` — generates + sends one daily message
- [ ] Build `services/streakService.js` — streak increment/reset logic
- [ ] Build `jobs/streakCheckJob.js` — nightly scan to reset stale streaks
- [ ] Test: register 5 test users with different delivery times, verify messages arrive on schedule
- [ ] Test: simulate streak scenarios (active, missed 1 day, missed 2 days)

